that night and told the truth.

106
00:13:52,252 --> 00:13:53,091
But you didn't.

107
00:13:54,652 --> 00:13:58,252
For Ge Wenjun,
you've abandoned your conscience.

108
00:13:59,731 --> 00:14:02,372
You clearly knew I would get hurt.

109
00:14:03,132 --> 00:14:05,372
Yet you chose to collude with her.

110
00:14:06,851 --> 00:14:09,611
Your cowardice is worse than lying.

111
00:14:12,811 --> 00:14:14,532
So I'll never forgive you.

112
00:14:16,412 --> 00:14:19,731
Nor do I believe
you'll carry the guilt forever.

113
00:14:21,372 --> 00:14:24,451
Selfish people excel
at forgiving themselves.

114
00:14:25,731 --> 00:14:26,731
Hope to see you again.

115
00:14:28,252 --> 00:14:29,211
I won't hope so.

116
00:14:30,451 --> 00:14:31,491
I won't see you again.

117
00:14:41,811 --> 00:14:45,912
(The past is the past.
The future remains in my hands.)

118
00:14:47,292 --> 00:14:50,731
(Heartbreak is an illness.
I think I've recovered from it.)

119
00:14:51,132 --> 00:14:52,491
What are you thinking about?

120
00:14:53,412 --> 00:14:56,216
Have you prepared well for the TOEFL?
It's next month, right?

121
00:14:57,132 --> 00:14:58,932
So you're going to study abroad?

122
00:15:02,091 --> 00:15:06,412
Mr. Liu sent me school listings there
and sorted out majors.

123
00:15:07,052 --> 00:15:08,172
I already have direction.

124
00:15:09,172 --> 00:15:10,571
